title: The Fifth Queen
creator: Ford Madox Ford
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Fifth Queen by Ford Madox Ford. Read by Elizabeth Klett. The Fifth Queen trilogy is a series of connected historical novels by English novelist Ford Madox Ford. It consists of three novels, The Fifth Queen; And How She Came to Court (1906), Privy Seal (1907) and The Fifth Queen Crowned (1908), which present a highly fictionalized account of Katharine Howard's marriage to King Henry VIII. (Summary by Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (209MB)
